trans-unit.source: Exception occurs if input datasets passed to the module should have compatible column types but do not.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs if input datasets passed to the module should have compatible column types but do not.

trans-unit.source: You will receive this error if the types of the columns passed in two or more datasets are not compatible with each other.
trans-unit.target: You will receive this error if the types of the columns passed in two or more datasets are not compatible with each other.

trans-unit.source: Use <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">metadata editor</link>, modify the original input dataset, or use <link xlink:href="72bf58e0-fc87-4bb1-9704-f1805003b975" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">convert to dataset</link> to ensure that the types of the columns are compatible.
trans-unit.target: Use <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">metadata editor</link>, modify the original input dataset, or use <link xlink:href="72bf58e0-fc87-4bb1-9704-f1805003b975" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">convert to dataset</link> to ensure that the types of the columns are compatible.

trans-unit.source: Columns with corresponding index in input datasets do have incompatible types.
trans-unit.target: Columns with corresponding index in input datasets do have incompatible types.

trans-unit.source: Column element types are not compatible for column {0} (zero-based) of input datasets ({1} and {2} respectively).
